WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.540 --> 00:00:01.800
- Let's say you're exploring ways

2
00:00:01.800 --> 00:00:03.600
to improve your company's services.

3
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:05.550
So you collect some survey data,

4
00:00:05.550 --> 00:00:07.590
pull reports on customer retention,

5
00:00:07.590 --> 00:00:09.540
and grab meeting notes
from your colleagues.

6
00:00:09.540 --> 00:00:12.030
Before you know it, they
have a lot to work with.

7
00:00:12.030 --> 00:00:14.340
But now, you've got a
different kind of challenge.

8
00:00:14.340 --> 00:00:16.230
With all of these different sources,

9
00:00:16.230 --> 00:00:18.120
how do you make sense of it all?

10
00:00:18.120 --> 00:00:20.580
Not everyone has training
on how to analyze data,

11
00:00:20.580 --> 00:00:21.840
and even for those that do,

12
00:00:21.840 --> 00:00:25.740
it isn't always easy to pull
clear insights from raw data.

13
00:00:25.740 --> 00:00:28.800
But data analysis can be an
incredibly valuable tool.

14
00:00:28.800 --> 00:00:29.633
Why?

15
00:00:29.633 --> 00:00:31.710
Because data can help you make the best

16
00:00:31.710 --> 00:00:33.570
and most informed decisions,

17
00:00:33.570 --> 00:00:34.950
and it can provide support

18
00:00:34.950 --> 00:00:37.230
for your point of view on any given issue.

19
00:00:37.230 --> 00:00:38.280
Now, with AI,

20
00:00:38.280 --> 00:00:40.650
even people whose eyes
would normally glaze over

21
00:00:40.650 --> 00:00:42.090
at the site of a spreadsheet

22
00:00:42.090 --> 00:00:45.120
can take advantage of the
power of data insights.

23
00:00:45.120 --> 00:00:48.660
Gemini can take messy data and
tell you what it all means.

24
00:00:48.660 --> 00:00:49.493
It can even make sense

25
00:00:49.493 --> 00:00:51.210
of different types of
data at the same time,

26
00:00:51.210 --> 00:00:54.270
like customer retention
numbers and survey feedback.

27
00:00:54.270 --> 00:00:56.610
AI can make the most frustrating

28
00:00:56.610 --> 00:00:58.740
and time-consuming parts of data analysis

29
00:00:58.740 --> 00:01:01.050
just fade into the background.

30
00:01:01.050 --> 00:01:02.670
You can even create visualizations

31
00:01:02.670 --> 00:01:04.500
to communicate your findings.

32
00:01:04.500 --> 00:01:07.320
You can also do more
complex analysis in new ways

33
00:01:07.320 --> 00:01:10.560
using everyday language
with Gemini in Sheets,

34
00:01:10.560 --> 00:01:12.210
and you can accelerate data cleaning

35
00:01:12.210 --> 00:01:15.510
and uncover patterns between
different data sources.

36
00:01:15.510 --> 00:01:19.140
It'll even troubleshoot
complicated formulas for you.

37
00:01:19.140 --> 00:01:21.900
All this means that you can
discover valuable insights

38
00:01:21.900 --> 00:01:25.080
in a fraction of the time
it would normally take.

39
00:01:25.080 --> 00:01:26.227
Now, you might be thinking,

40
00:01:26.227 --> 00:01:28.860
"If Gemini can do all
this analysis for me,

41
00:01:28.860 --> 00:01:30.480
what do I have to do?"

42
00:01:30.480 --> 00:01:32.550
Well, first you still have to ask

43
00:01:32.550 --> 00:01:34.680
really good questions about the data.

44
00:01:34.680 --> 00:01:36.480
Sometimes it helps to start broad

45
00:01:36.480 --> 00:01:37.920
to understand the biggest trends

46
00:01:37.920 --> 00:01:39.570
and the most important conclusions,

47
00:01:39.570 --> 00:01:42.330
and then drill down into the details.

48
00:01:42.330 --> 00:01:44.190
Second, if you make a discovery

49
00:01:44.190 --> 00:01:46.260
or find an interesting insight,

50
00:01:46.260 --> 00:01:48.810
it's really up to you to
understand the implications

51
00:01:48.810 --> 00:01:51.300
and make the right business decisions.

52
00:01:51.300 --> 00:01:54.120
And lastly, you'll always
need to verify the findings

53
00:01:54.120 --> 00:01:56.580
to ensure their accuracy.

54
00:01:56.580 --> 00:01:59.370
Another thing to consider is data privacy.

55
00:01:59.370 --> 00:02:00.660
The goal and rule is simple,

56
00:02:00.660 --> 00:02:04.830
never input confidential
data into a public AI tool

57
00:02:04.830 --> 00:02:07.050
and always consult your company's policies

58
00:02:07.050 --> 00:02:09.570
on acceptable use of AI tools.

59
00:02:09.570 --> 00:02:12.240
Now, if you do need to
work with sensitive data,

60
00:02:12.240 --> 00:02:13.920
you have two main options.

61
00:02:13.920 --> 00:02:17.700
First, see if your company has
an enterprise-grade AI tool.

62
00:02:17.700 --> 00:02:19.620
The second option is to check the settings

63
00:02:19.620 --> 00:02:21.510
of the public tool that you're using.

64
00:02:21.510 --> 00:02:23.700
You can opt out of data collection

65
00:02:23.700 --> 00:02:26.310
or adjust your privacy controls as needed.

66
00:02:26.310 --> 00:02:29.190
Understanding these controls
isn't just about privacy,

67
00:02:29.190 --> 00:02:31.320
it's about giving you the
knowledge and confidence

68
00:02:31.320 --> 00:02:33.660
to analyze data with AI.

69
00:02:33.660 --> 00:02:34.830
By the end of this course,

70
00:02:34.830 --> 00:02:36.270
you'll be able to use Gemini

71
00:02:36.270 --> 00:02:38.460
to discover the most critical insights

72
00:02:38.460 --> 00:02:40.980
hidden in an ocean of data.

73
00:02:40.980 --> 00:02:42.543
So, let's dive in.